# React Conventions

## Component Structure

Use functional components with named exports. Keep pages in `src/pages/`, shared UI in `src/components/`.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — named export, typed props
export function RecipeCard({ recipe }: { recipe: UserRecipe }) {
  return <div className="...">{recipe.title}</div>;
}
```

## Data Fetching — React Query

Define custom hooks in `src/hooks/`. Use typed wrappers from `src/api/`.

```tsx
// src/hooks/useRecipes.ts
export function useMyRecipes() {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ['recipes', 'mine'],
    queryFn: () => api.get<UserRecipe[]>('/api/recipes/mine'),
  });
}

// src/hooks/useSaveRecipe.ts
export function useSaveRecipe() {
  const queryClient = useQueryClient();
  return useMutation({
    mutationFn: (sourceId: number) => api.post(`/api/recipes/source/${sourceId}/save`),
    onSuccess: () => queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['recipes', 'mine'] }),
  });
}
```

## API Client

Typed fetch wrappers live in `src/api/`. Always include auth token from cookie.

```tsx
// src/api/index.ts
export const api = {
  get: <T>(path: string) => fetch(path, { headers: authHeaders() }).then(r => r.json() as Promise<T>),
  post: <T>(path: string, body?: unknown) => fetch(path, { method: 'POST', body: JSON.stringify(body), headers: authHeaders() }).then(r => r.json() as Promise<T>),
};
```

## Loading / Error States

Every page must handle loading and error states explicitly:

```tsx
const { data, isLoading, isError } = useMyRecipes();
if (isLoading) return <Spinner />;
if (isError) return <ErrorMessage />;
```

## msw Mocks

Handlers live in `src/mocks/handlers.ts` and are shared between tests and optional dev mode.

```tsx
// src/mocks/handlers.ts
export const handlers = [
  http.get('/api/recipes/mine', () => HttpResponse.json([mockRecipe])),
];
```

## Co-located Tests

Test files sit next to the component they test:

```
RecipeDetail.tsx
RecipeDetail.test.tsx   ← same directory
```
